model_explanation: if Sam only gave Ellen grapes, it means no one else, including Tom, received grapes. This entails that Sam didn't give Tom grapes.
if Sam only gave Ellen apples, it means apples were the only things given to Ellen, so no oranges were given, which entails that Sam didn’t give Ellen oranges.

saying Sam only gave Rob grapes means Rob was the exclusive recipient of grapes, while the second sentence says Ellen also received grapes. These statements are independent because one is specifying exclusivity around Rob, while the other is mentioning an additional recipient.

the first sentence restricts the giving of apples to only Rob, and the second says Ellen also got apples. Both statements are independent as they discuss different possible distributions, without direct logical contradiction.
